## 📋 Short Summary

> **FundIQ** is an AI-powered Mutual Fund Portfolio Intelligence Platform. It lets users track their mutual fund investments in real-time, see live NAV prices from AMFI, visualize their portfolio allocation through interactive charts, calculate SIP projections, and get AI-driven risk scores and rebalancing suggestions — all behind a secure JWT auth system.

---

## 📖 The Long Story — *How FundIQ Came to Life*

---

It started with a frustration most Indian investors know all too well.

Ronak was juggling five different mutual fund apps — one for NAVs, one for SIP tracking, a spreadsheet for P&L, and a calculator bookmarked somewhere he could never find quickly. Every Monday morning, he'd piece together the full picture of his portfolio manually, cross-referencing numbers, asking himself: *"Am I actually growing? Is my portfolio too risky? Should I be putting more in equity?"*

The answer was always buried somewhere in the noise.

So he decided to build **FundIQ** — not just another fund tracker, but an intelligent portfolio copilot.

---

### 🏗️ Building the Foundation

The journey began with a **Node.js + Express** backend, carefully structured with Mongoose models for two core entities: the `User` and their `Portfolio` holdings. MongoDB Atlas was chosen as the database for its flexibility with nested documents — perfect for storing a list of fund holdings with SIP toggles and unit counts.

Security was non-negotiable from day one. Passwords were hashed with **bcryptjs** before ever touching the database, and every authenticated route was gated behind **JWT Bearer Tokens**. Even the registration flow included a `riskProfile` selection — conservative, moderate, or aggressive — baked right into the user model.

---

### 📡 Connecting to the Real World

The magic behind FundIQ's live data? A simple but powerful truth — AMFI (Association of Mutual Funds in India) publishes the NAV of every registered mutual fund daily, and **mfapi.in** makes it beautifully accessible via REST.

The backend built two critical endpoints:
- **`/api/portfolio/search?q=...`** — queries 10,000+ AMFI funds in milliseconds
- **`/api/portfolio/nav/:code`** — fetches the real-time NAV for any scheme code

No third-party paid APIs. No rate limits. Just clean, live data from the source.

`node-cron` was wired in to handle scheduled background jobs — ensuring NAV data could be refreshed systematically even without user interaction.

---

### ⚛️ The React Frontend — Where It All Comes Alive

The frontend was scaffolded with **Vite + React 19**, chosen for its blazing-fast hot module replacement during development. **TailwindCSS v4** powered the design system — a dark fintech aesthetic with glassmorphism cards, gradient accents, and a sidebar layout that felt premium from the first click.

**React Router DOM v7** connected six distinct pages:

- **`/login`** — A sleek auth page where users sign up with their risk profile
- **`/dashboard`** — The nerve center: real-time portfolio stats, AI suggestions, and allocation charts
- **`/portfolio`** — A full table of holdings with invested value, current NAV, units, P&L, and return %
- **`/add-fund`** — Live search through AMFI's 10,000+ funds with SIP toggle
- **`/sip-calculator`** — An interactive SIP projection tool with sliders and an animated line chart
- **`/insights`** — The AI brain: risk score (0–100), radar chart for diversification, and rebalancing targets

**Framer Motion** breathed life into every page transition, card entrance, and data update. **Chart.js** rendered four different chart types — donut for allocation, bar for category breakdown, line for SIP projections, and radar for the diversification map.

An **AuthContext** managed JWT tokens globally, with **Axios interceptors** automatically attaching the Bearer token to every API call. If a token expired, the user was cleanly redirected to login.

**React Hot Toast** handled all feedback notifications — from "Fund added successfully!" to "Invalid credentials" — ensuring users were never left wondering what just happened.

---

### 🤖 The "AI" Layer — Smart Without an LLM

FundIQ's AI features are deliberately rule-based and deterministic — no external AI API needed, no hallucinations, no latency.

The **AI Risk Score** (0–100) is calculated server-side based on the user's actual fund allocation:
- Equity-heavy portfolios push the score higher
- Debt and liquid funds pull it down
- The score updates live as holdings change

The **AI Suggestions** engine reads the portfolio composition and generates diversification recommendations — "You're overweight in large-cap equity, consider adding a debt fund for balance" — based on the user's declared risk profile.

The **Portfolio Rebalance** tool suggests target allocation percentages across asset classes based on risk tolerance, then shows the gap between where the portfolio is and where it should be.

All of this without a single API call to OpenAI or any external AI service. Just clean financial logic, well-executed.

---

### 🚀 Deployment — Taking It Live

The project was deployed on **Vercel** — with a custom [vercel.json](file:///d:/Antigravity%20Projects/FundIQ/vercel.json) configuration routing all API calls through the Express backend and all client-side routes falling back to the React SPA.

After resolving ESLint build errors and Vercel configuration challenges (a journey documented in its own right across multiple debug sessions), FundIQ went live — accessible from anywhere, with a real MongoDB Atlas cluster serving real data.

---

### 🎯 What FundIQ Represents

FundIQ isn't just a personal finance tool. It's a **full-stack showcase** — demonstrating mastery of:
- Secure JWT-based auth flows
- Real-time third-party API integration
- Complex data visualization with multiple chart types
- AI logic without external AI dependencies
- Production deployment on Vercel with proper routing

It's the kind of project that answers the question every investor asks on Monday morning — *"How am I actually doing?"* — in one clean, intelligent, beautifully designed dashboard.

